-- ⚠️ RE-PINNED 2026-07-14 — THE S2 INVERSION.  `size 3` now prints 4, was "IMPL".
-- The definer shadow `size : Int -> Int` wins over `impl Sz Int`; the impl universe is
-- not consulted.  Everything below describes the OLD rule (kept for the history).
--
-- P0-20 (peer of p0_20_shadow_literal_receiver, with a USER interface so the cell is
-- readable without prelude knowledge, and with a method whose RESULT TYPE DIFFERS from
-- the standalone's — which is what makes the disagreement observable rather than merely
-- theoretical).
--
-- `size` is a definer shadow whose declared domain (`Int`) is ALSO the head of a live
-- impl (`impl Sz Int`).  Per SHADOW-SEMANTICS S2 a grounded receiver with a visible impl
-- DISPATCHES, so `size 3` is the method: `"IMPL"`, not `4`.
--
-- Before the fix: check typed it Int (standalone), run panicked, build printed a raw
-- POINTER (`47059475956112`) — a String cell read as an Int.
interface Sz a where
  size : a -> String

impl Sz Int where
  size n = "IMPL"

size : Int -> Int
size n = n + 1

main = println (size 3)
